label.value: mammary gland epithelial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized epithelial cell becomes a more specialized epithelial cell of the mammary gland.

label.value: mesenchymal cell condensation involved in mammary fat development

value.value: The cell adhesion process in which mammary mesenchyme cells adhere to one another in the initial stages of the formation of mammary fat development.

label.value: mammary gland bud morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which anatomical structures of the mammary gland buds are generated and organized. Mammary gland buds form by an outpocketing of the mammary placodes and grow to invade the mammary fat, when they form the mammary cord.

label.value: mammary gland bud elongation

value.value: The process in which the mammary gland bud grows along its axis.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in mammary gland bud elongation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mammary gland bud epithelial cells, resulting in the elongation of the bud.

label.value: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in mammary gland bud elongation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mammary gland bud epithelial cell proliferation that results in the elongation of the bud.

label.value: mammary gland cord morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which anatomical structures of the mammary gland cord are generated and organized. Mammary gland cords form when the mammary gland bud invades the mammary fat.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in mammary gland cord morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized epithelial cell becomes a more specialized epithelial cell of the mammary gland cord. Epithelial cells of the mammary cord give it its funnel-like shape and some are cornified.

label.value: branching involved in mammary gland cord morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the branching structure of the mammary gland cord is generated and organized. The mammary gland cord is a solid epithelial structure that will hollow out, forming the mammary duct.

label.value: nipple morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the nipple is generated and organized.

label.value: nipple sheath formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the nipple sheath from the unspecified epidermis. This process begins with a circular ingrowth of the epidermis around the region of the mammary sprout. It ends before the region begins to elevate.

label.value: epidermis morphogenesis involved in nipple formation

value.value: The process in which the epidermis of the nipple sheath is uplifted to form an umbrella-like projection.

label.value: submandibular salivary gland formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a submandibular salivary gland. This process begins with a thickening of the epithelium next to the tongue and ends when a bud linked to the oral surface is formed.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in salivary gland morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells of the submandibular salivary gland, resulting in the expansion of a cell population and the shaping of the gland.

label.value: embryonic placenta morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the embryonic placenta is generated and organized.

label.value: branching involved in labyrinthine layer morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the branches of the fetal placental villi are generated and organized. The villous part of the placenta is called the labyrinth layer.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The process in which a trophoblast cell acquires specialized features of an epithelial cell of the placental labyrinthine layer.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in placenta development

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another.

label.value: placenta blood vessel development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a blood vessel of the placenta over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: ureteric bud morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the ureteric bud is generated and organized.

label.value: ureteric bud formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the ureteric bud from the Wolffian duct. This process begins when the bud protrudes from the duct and ends when it is a recognizable bud.

label.value: ureteric bud elongation

value.value: The developmental growth in which the ureteric bud grows along its axis beginning with the growth of the primary ureteric bud and ending when the branches of the bud have elongated.

label.value: lateral sprouting involved in ureteric bud morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which a branch forms along the side of a ureteric bud.

label.value: epithelial-mesenchymal cell signaling

value.value: Any process that results in the transfer of information from an epithelial cell to a mesenchymal cell where it is interpreted.

label.value: regulation of prostatic bud formation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of prostatic bud formation, the morphogenetic process in which a region of the fetal urogenital sinus epithelium is specified to become the prostate, resulting in prostate bud outgrowth.

label.value: negative regulation of prostatic bud formation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of prostatic bud formation, the morphogenetic process in which a region of the fetal urogenital sinus epithelium is specified to become the prostate, resulting in prostate bud outgrowth.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in prostate gland morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of prostate gland branching, the process in which the branching structure of the prostate gland is generated and organized. A branch is a division or offshoot from a main stem.

label.value: regulation of morphogenesis of a branching structure

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of branches are generated and organized.

label.value: cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells of the salivary gland.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquire specialized structural and/or functional features of an epithelial cell of the salivary gland.

label.value: epithelial cell maturation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an epithelial cell of the salivary gland to attain its fully functional state.

label.value: mesenchymal cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a mesenchymal cell of the salivary gland. A mesenchymal cell is a loosely associated cell that is part of the connective tissue in an organism. Mesenchymal cells give rise to more mature connective tissue cell types.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in salivary gland morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching morphogenesis in the salivary gland epithelium.

label.value: regulation of phospholipid catabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of phospholipid catabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phospholipids, any lipid containing phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester.

label.value: positive regulation of phospholipid catabolic process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of phospholipid catabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phospholipids, any lipid containing phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester.

label.value: acinar cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize an acinar cell of the salivary gland. Acinar cells are protein-secreting cells in the gland.

label.value: neuron differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the neurons of the salivary gland.

label.value: cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of the embryonic placenta.

label.value: spongiotrophoblast differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell of the ectoplacental cone acquires specialized features of a spongiotrophoblast of the placenta. A spongiotrophoblast cell is a basophilic cell.

label.value: chorio-allantoic fusion

value.value: The cell-cell adhesion process in which the cells of the chorion fuse to the cells of the allantois.

label.value: labyrinthine layer development

value.value: The process in which the labyrinthine layer of the placenta progresses, from its formation to its mature state.

label.value: spongiotrophoblast layer development

value.value: The process in which the spongiotrophoblast layer of the placenta progresses from its formation to its mature state.

label.value: labyrinthine layer morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the labyrinthine layer of the placenta is generated and organized.

label.value: labyrinthine layer formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the labyrinthine layer of the placenta.

label.value: labyrinthine layer blood vessel development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a blood vessel of the labyrinthine layer of the placenta over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The embryonic vessels grow through the layer to come in close contact with the maternal blood supply.

label.value: chorion development

value.value: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a chorion from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the structure and ends with the mature structure. The chorion is an extraembryonic membrane.

label.value: chorionic trophoblast cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells of the ectoplacental cone acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize chorionic trophoblasts. These cells will migrate towards the spongiotrophoblast layer and give rise to syncytiotrophoblasts of the labyrinthine layer.

label.value: chorionic trophoblast cell development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the chorionic trophoblast over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a specific fate.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the embryonic placenta.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development.
